# Testing (Vitest)

- Co-locate tests: `foo.ts` → `foo.test.ts`
- Use `describe`, `it`, `expect` from vitest
- Pure lib code: test directly; no mocks needed for isolated functions
- Components/hooks: use @testing-library/react; render, screen, userEvent
- Run `npm run test:run` to verify tests pass

## Example

```typescript
import { describe, it, expect } from "vitest";
import { myFunction } from "./my-module";

describe("myFunction", () => {
  it("returns expected value for valid input", () => {
    expect(myFunction("input")).toEqual(expected);
  });
});
```
